To compile: (in this order)
>>javac Client.java
>>javac Server.java
>>Javac Peer.java

The folder will then have the corresponding "*.class" files.

To run:
Open two terminals T1 and T2.
T1: java Peer <port_self> <port_friend> <username> <friendname>			( Command line arguments )
T2: java Peer <port_self> <port_friend> <username> <friendname>			( Command line arguments )

For example,
T1: java Peer 5000 6000 Alice Bob
T2: java Peer 6000 5000 Bob Alice

Wait for upto ten seconds for both systems to connect to the other, independently. Once both systems connect, use the following functionality.
Messaging: Type your message at a prompt (>>) and it will appear as a sent message on your friend's prompt.
File transfer:
1. TCP:
Format: Sending <filepath> TCP
2. UDP:
Format: Sending <filepath> UDP
